
[1]monopolizer

   MONOP'OLIZER, n. One that monopolizes; a person who engrosses a
   commodity by purchasing the whole of that article in market for the
   purpose of selling it at an advanced price; or one who has a license or
   privilege granted by authority, for the sole buying or selling of any
   commodity. The man who retains in his hands his own produce or
   manufacture, is not a monopolist within the meaning of the laws for
   preventing monopolies.
